TeaLow Documentation
=====================

TeaLow is a unified AI SDK for Python that lets you use Google Gemini, OpenAI, 
Anthropic Claude, and DeepSeek through one consistent API. Switch providers by 
changing the model name — no other code changes required.


HOW TO INSTALL
---------------

pip install TeaLow

Or install from source:

git clone https://github.com/tealow/tealow.git
cd tealow
pip install -e ".[dev]"

Requires Python 3.9 or higher.


HOW TO USE
-----------

1. Basic usage

from TeaLow import TeaLow

ai = TeaLow(
    model="gemini-2.5-flash",
    api="YOUR_API_KEY"
)

response = ai.send("Hello!")
print(response)

The same code works for any provider — just change the model and key:

ai = TeaLow(model="gpt-4o-mini", api="YOUR_OPENAI_KEY")
ai = TeaLow(model="claude-sonnet-4-6", api="YOUR_ANTHROPIC_KEY")
ai = TeaLow(model="deepseek-chat", api="YOUR_DEEPSEEK_KEY")


2. Using environment variables (no need to pass api=)

export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."

from TeaLow import TeaLow

ai = TeaLow(model="gpt-4o-mini")
print(ai.send("Hello!"))


3. Conversation history (multi-turn)

ai = TeaLow(model="claude-sonnet-4-6", api="YOUR_KEY", system_prompt="You are a helpful pirate.")

ai.send("What's your name?")
ai.send("What did I just ask you?")

for message in ai.history:
    print(message["role"], "->", message["content"])


4. Streaming responses

for chunk in ai.stream("Write a haiku about the ocean."):
    print(chunk.delta, end="", flush=True)


5. Async usage

import asyncio
from TeaLow import AsyncTeaLow

async def main():
    ai = AsyncTeaLow(model="gemini-2.5-flash", api="YOUR_KEY")
    response = await ai.send("Hello from asyncio!")
    print(response)

    async for chunk in ai.stream("Tell me a joke."):
        print(chunk.delta, end="")

    await ai.close()

asyncio.run(main())


6. Vision (image input)

ai = TeaLow(model="gpt-4o-mini", api="YOUR_KEY")
image = TeaLow.load_image(path="photo.jpg")
response = ai.send("What is in this image?", images=[image])
print(response)


7. JSON mode

response = ai.send(
    "Return a JSON object with keys 'name' and 'age' for a fictional person.",
    json_mode=True,
)
import json
data = json.loads(response.text)


8. Image generation

ai = TeaLow(model="dall-e-3", api="YOUR_OPENAI_KEY")
urls = ai.generate_image("A watercolor painting of a teapot on a low table")
print(urls[0])


9. Custom headers, proxy, and timeouts

ai = TeaLow(
    model="gpt-4o-mini",
    api="YOUR_KEY",
    timeout=30.0,
    max_retries=5,
    proxies={"https": "http://proxy.internal:8080"},
    headers={"X-Org-Id": "acme-corp"},
)


10. Logging

from TeaLow import configure_logging
import logging

configure_logging(level=logging.DEBUG)


11. Error handling

from TeaLow import TeaLow, RateLimitError, InvalidAPIKeyError, TeaLowError

ai = TeaLow(model="gpt-4o-mini", api="YOUR_KEY")

try:
    response = ai.send("Hello!")
except RateLimitError as e:
    print("Rate limited, retry after:", e.retry_after)
except InvalidAPIKeyError:
    print("Your API key was rejected.")
except TeaLowError as e:
    print("Something else went wrong:", e)


SUPPORTED MODELS
-----------------

Gemini    -> gemini-2.5-flash, gemini-2.5-pro          (detected by "gemini")
OpenAI    -> gpt-4o, gpt-4o-mini, o3, dall-e-3          (detected by "gpt-", "o1/o3/o4", "dall-e")
Anthropic -> claude-sonnet-4-6, claude-opus-4-8         (detected by "claude")
DeepSeek  -> deepseek-chat, deepseek-reasoner           (detected by "deepseek")


